Vice President Pence expressed his appreciation to the USMCA advisory council in Canada for their efforts in creating the largest trade deal in US history. He mentioned that both the US and Canada drove a hard bargain during the negotiations but believe that the USMCA is an idea whose time has come. Pence also stated that the US administration is working to get the USMCA approved by the Congress this summer. He emphasized that the agreement is superior to its predecessor and will benefit jobs, growth, working people, and investment in both countries. Pence thanked the council for their efforts and pledged to work closely with Canada and Mexico to finalize the USMCA this year.